examples.title: Error: Missing Header Option
Error: Invalid API Key

Parameter.description: The max number of objects returned. The max that will be honored by the api is 100.

Success 200.description: A key to reference for paginated results.
Tells the application if the request was successful.
The HTTP status code of the request, this is also available in the header.

Pagination.description: The max amount of results returned per request.
The next page available in url form.

User Object.description: The numeric id assigned to the user by the database.
The user's name prefix, if there is one.
The user's middle name or initial, if there is one.
The user's name postfix, if there is one.
The phonetic user's name, if there is one.
